race.comment: The stayers kick us off. CONNECTICUT (6) goes well for hoop Bayliss who has a win and four placings from just seven steers and will be rock-hard fit for this. Boasts a win around this circuit and should be in this contest for a long way. PUNJABI LANDING (4) has put back-to-back victories together including getting the job done over this course and distance two back. Maps ideally from gate two and should give backers a sight. KIRKEBY (1) has placed over this track and trip, draws low and gets plenty of weight relief with the 3kg claim. Ticks a few boxes for a race like this. CHASSAGNE (5) saves her best form for this distance range and gets the services of Maloney in the irons. Don't discount lightly. OLD SONG (9) rounds out the selections.
